quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  109,1,"Say, “O disbelievers,"
  109,2,"I do not worship what you worship,"
  109,3,"nor do you worship what I worship."
  109,4,"Never will I worship what you worship,"
  109,5,"nor will you ever worship what I worship."
  109,6,"You have your religion and I have my religion.""
  110,1,"When there comes Allah’s help and the conquest,"
  110,2,"and you see people entering Allah’s religion in multitudes,"
  110,3,"then glorify the praise of your Lord, and ask His forgiveness. Indeed, He is ever Accepting of Repentance."
  111,1,"May the hands of Abu Lahab perish, and may he perish!"
  111,2,"Neither his wealth nor his worldly gains will avail him."
  111,3,"He will burn in a Flaming Fire,"
  111,4,"and so will his wife, the carrier of firewood,"
  111,5,"around her neck will be a rope of palm fiber."